      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Separate the<strong> white duck fat </strong>and the <strong>duck</strong> <strong>jelly</strong> from the <strong>duck</strong> <strong>leg[s]</strong> and save for later</p><p>Add the <strong>hasselback</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) with the <strong>white</strong> <strong>duck</strong> <strong>fat</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 35-40 min or until tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
